messages.content: ComfyUI-CascadeResolutions is a custom node for ComfyUI that allows users to select the x and y sizes from a list when generating images.

To install ComfyUI-CascadeResolutions, navigate to the 'custom_nodes' directory in your ComfyUI installation, and run the command 'git clone https://github.com/GavChap/ComfyUI-CascadeResolutions .' in your terminal.
What new node is added to ComfyUI after installing ComfyUI-CascadeResolutions?
After installing ComfyUI-CascadeResolutions, a new node called 'Cascade Resolutions' will be available in ComfyUI.
What options does the Cascade Resolutions node provide?
The Cascade Resolutions node allows users to pick the x and y sizes from a predefined list when generating images in ComfyUI.
Is there a visual preview available for the Cascade Resolutions node?
Yes, a visual preview of the Cascade Resolutions node is available at https://github.com/al-swaiti/ComfyUI-CascadeResolutions/blob/main/preview.png.
Who is the author of the ComfyUI-CascadeResolutions custom node?
The author of the ComfyUI-CascadeResolutions custom node is GavChap, as seen from the GitHub repository URL.
Can I select custom x and y sizes using the Cascade Resolutions node?
No, the Cascade Resolutions node only allows selecting x and y sizes from a predefined list, not custom sizes.
